caption: b'From the Payne Stewart Award in September, to playing the @themasters in November, @zjohnsonpga is ending 2020 on a high note. Hit \xe2\x80\x98em straight this weekend!'
b'Hey @bernhard.langer, have room for another green jacket? We\xe2\x80\x99re looking forward to watching you this weekend @themasters!'
b'Let\xe2\x80\x99s add a green jacket to this gray shirt! We\xe2\x80\x99re rooting for you this weekend at @themasters :flag_in_hole: @mattkuchargolf'

b'As part of our $50 million HBCU initiative, we are awarding grants to support technology for 21 historically black colleges and universities. We are honored to partner with some of the country\xe2\x80\x99s top institutions of higher learning as we invest in the next generation of technology leaders. Link in bio.'
b'White-nose syndrome has haunted the bat population since 2006. With our partners @nfwf and @batconservationinternational, we are helping slow the spread. Happy #BatWeek! #SOconservation'
b'We received the Military Spouse Friendly Employers award by G.I. Jobs magazine for our efforts in creating sustainable and meaningful career paths for military spouses. Link in bio.'

b'To kick off National Drive Electric Week, we\xe2\x80\x99re announcing our internal fleet electrification goal. Converting to electric is a win-win for drivers, communities, businesses and the environment. Learn more using link in bio. #DriveElectricWeek'

b'Powering the future of energy through wind. @southernpowerco currently owns or operates more than 2,115 megawatts of wind generating capacity at 13 facilities operating or under construction. #NCEW20'
b'Today, we issued a road map on how we will achieve net zero greenhouse gas emissions by 2050. Read more on our plan for a net zero future using the link in bio.'
b'Congratulations to @djohnsonpga\xe2\x80\x94 yesterday\xe2\x80\x99s winner of @playofffinale and the @fedex Cup. We are thankful to be a part of TOUR Championship each year!'

b'The Payne Stewart Award ceremony is one of our favorite parts of @playofffinale week and last night was no different. \n\nCongratulations, Zach, what a special person and player you are on and off the course.'

b'The Payne Stewart Award ceremony will be televised live tonight on @golfchannel at 6:30 p.m. EST. Alongside @pgatour, we are proud to honor Zach Johnson with the Payne Stewart Award presented by Southern Company. Congratulations, Zach! You deserve it.'

b'They\xe2\x80\x99re back! As a Proud Partner of @playofffinale, we are excited to welcome the top 30 players back to Atlanta for TOUR Championship 2020. Who\xe2\x80\x99s your pick? :trophy::man_golfing_medium_skin_tone:'
b'We are ONE week away from @playofffinale! As a Proud Partner, Southern Company is once again excited to welcome TOUR Championship home to Atlanta.'

b'Skookumchuck Wind Facility is well on its way to achieving commercial operation. In the meantime, we\xe2\x80\x99re enjoying this amazing shot taken from the T-21 turbine pad looking toward Mount Rainier and the T-25 turbine. @southernpowerco'

b'Nearly a thousand Southern Company system resources responded to help restore power in the Northeast after Tropical Storm Isaias battered the region, leaving more than 3.5 million customers without power from South Carolina to New England. Story link in bio.'

b'Congratulations to Zach Johnson, the 2020 recipient of the Payne Stewart Award. You truly embody Payne\xe2\x80\x99s values of character, charity and sportsmanship on and off the course. We, alongside, @pgatour look forward to presenting you with this award! Link in bio.'

b'We will always remember what Rep. John Lewis taught us during his lifelong fight for racial equality, human rights and social justice. Our company honors his legacy by applying these lessons through our actions and marching in support of equality and fairness for all.'

b'Engaging with the environmental community has fostered a remarkable relationship between our company and Sister Barbara Aires and Sister Pat Daly. Together, we are working to achieving Southern Company\xe2\x80\x99s net-zero carbon goal. Link in bio to read this story.'

b'PRIDE Power and Spectrum are two employee resource groups within Southern Company dedicated to promoting equality and encouraging LGBTQ+ employees to be their true, authentic selves at work. Meet the two leaders of these groups and what Pride means to each. Link in bio.'

b'For the 14th consecutive year, we have been named one of the 2020 Best Places to Work in IT. Acquiring and developing top IT talent is more important than ever and key to helping us successfully build the future of energy! #BestPlacesIT Link in bio.'
b'We are remembering, reflecting and continually learning. Read our letter to our colleagues using the link in bio. #Juneteenth'
b'We must realize that there is more work to be done and that we are being called to do it. Read more using the link in bio.'
b'#blackouttuesday'

b'Today, we announced our enterprise-wide transition to a goal of net zero carbon emissions by 2050 from our 2018 low-to-no carbon goal. We will continue to reduce our greenhouse gas emissions and continue our long-term commitment to energy efficiency, but also incorporate negative carbon solutions, including technology-based approaches. #SOAnnualMeeting link in bio.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9c2019 was an excellent year as we remain among the industry\xe2\x80\x99s leaders for operational performance and customer satisfaction. I am proud of our performance and I am proud to be part of the great Southern Company team.\xe2\x80\x9d Tom Fanning, CEO of Southern Company #SOAnnualMeeting'

b'The team at Vogtle Units 3 and 4 has worked incredibly hard to create an environment at the site that has led to meaningful progress over the past few months, even while managing through this unprecedented pandemic. Today, Unit 3 direct construction is more than 90% complete and Unit 4 is approximately 68% complete. #SOAnnualMeeting'
b'Strengthening our commitment to energy innovation, we have expanded our focus for the National Carbon Capture Center in partnership with the U.S. Department of Energy. Link in bio.'

b'Meet Aaron Myers local area manager at @mississippipower. During a series of tornadoes in April, Aaron\xe2\x80\x99s home was hit and damaged\xe2\x80\x94but that did not stop his commitment to our customers and communities. These are the Faces of Our Front Line.'

b'Across Southern Company, we have never stopped working during the COVID-19 pandemic as we continue to serve our 9 million customers every day. Read more about our commitment to our customers, colleagues and communities using the link in bio.'

b'Southern Company ranks number 26 on @diversityinc\xe2\x80\x99s 2020 Top 50 Companies for Diversity list, the fifth consecutive year we have been recognized for diversity and inclusion, including our efforts to hire, retain and promote women, minorities, people with disabilities, LGBTQ and veterans. Link in bio.'
b'@usnavyblueangels and @afthunderbirds salute front line workers :blue_heart: Thank you to those who continue serving our communities through it all, including many of our own colleagues.'
b'Today, we released our first-quarter 2020 earnings. View the full report using the link in bio.'
b'A special thanks from Matt Kuchar to our linemen, who work hard each day to keep our communities energized. #LinemanAppreciationMonth'

b'Happy Earth Day! Southern Company and its subsidiaries are proud to support the communities we serve and are committed to protecting and conserving the environment we all share. #EarthDay link in bio.'
b'From our family to yours, we are in this together.'
b'Let\xe2\x80\x99s do this, together. Continue to slow the spread of the coronavirus.'
b'Explore Southern Company\xe2\x80\x99s River Scout Gallery from your own home! What is your favorite freshwater creature? @georgiaaquarium link in bio.'

b'In order to comply with recommendations from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention during the COVID-19 pandemic and for the safety of our stockholders and employees, this year\xe2\x80\x99s annual meeting of stockholders will be a virtual meeting on Wednesday, May 27 at 10 a.m. ET in lieu of our customary in-person meeting.'
b'Southern Company\xe2\x80\x99s 2019 Annual Report and 2020 Proxy Statement are available for viewing. Link in bio.'
b'We stand with our communities to help slow the spread of COVID-19. #PoweringThruTogether'
b'Thank you to those on the front lines, including many of our employees, during the coronavirus pandemic. #LightItBlue'

b'Across the Southern Company system, employees are working to stay safe while providing reliable energy to customers who need it, including the healthcare industry and those sick. #PoweringThruTogether\nLink in bio.'

b'An unlikely partnership between Southern Company and Atlanta\xe2\x80\x99s Old Fourth Ward Distillery is helping meet our system\xe2\x80\x99s need for hand sanitizer. We are #PoweringThruTogether with local businesses and organizations. Link in bio.'

b'Lunch Table: Episode 3 brings together female leaders from across the system to continue the discussion of company culture, diversity and inclusion and more using Women\xe2\x80\x99s History Month as a backdrop. Full video link in bio.'

b'North America\xe2\x80\x99s Building Trades Union: \xe2\x80\x9cWe commend the extraordinary measures taken by Southern Company at Plant Vogtle to go above and beyond the call of duty to keep our members safe and healthy.\xe2\x80\x9d Link in bio. \n#BuildingTradesWhateverItTakes #PoweringThruTogether'

b'Today, and every day, we are thankful for our medical services personnel and their dedication to the health and safety of our employees. We appreciate the diligence of medical professionals across the world fighting through the uncertainty of the coronavirus to serve others. #NationalDoctorsDay'

b'The Southern Company system has pledged $4.85 million to coronavirus (COVID-19) relief through combined donations from @alabamapower, @ga_power, @mississippipower and @southerncogas\xe2\x80\x99 foundations. In addition to monetary donations, each company announced it would temporarily suspend service disconnections for its customers. Link in bio.'

b'Fran Forehand, vice president of customer service and operations at @mississippipower, empowers the future generation of leaders through her servant leadership. #EachForEqual #WomensHistoryMonth Hear more of Fran\xe2\x80\x99s story using link in bio.'

b'Southern Company continues its commitment to our veterans through partnership with the Department of Defense SkillBridge Program. We celebrate employees like Victoria Ollo and the value they bring to our team. Link in bio.'

b'As the impact of the coronavirus pandemic continues, the Southern Company system is assuring customers there are comprehensive plans and procedures in place to help ensure service continues. Learn more using link in bio.'

b'Much like how we respond to hurricanes and other storms, it is times like these when we are the ones who are called to act for the benefit of our customers, our communities and the nation as a whole. We will continue to keep the lights on and the energy flowing throughout the coronavirus situation. Link in bio.'

b'An impressive roster of employees was selected as recipients of the Technology Transfer Award from the Electric Power Research Institute (EPRI) for their achievements in collaborative research and development projects for the 22nd year! Link in bio.'
b'Heidi Wease, @ga_power apprentice lineman, is setting the pace for women who want to work as a member of a line crew. #womenshistorymonth #eachforequal link in bio.'

b'Lunch Table is an unscripted dialogue series where our employees are having free-flowing, candid conversations about today\xe2\x80\x99s important cultural matters. Enjoy the first episode and hear from executives across the system as they discuss culture, diversity and inclusion, and more. Link in bio.'
b'Wishing competitors in the U.S. Olympic Marathon Trials a safe and successful race! Southern Company is happy to have the Olympic spirit back in Atlanta.'
b'It\xe2\x80\x99s a feel-good Friday! Thank you, Shane and Dwayne, @ga_power linemen, for being a citizen where you serve and rescuing these puppies. We are happy to see they are safe and sound!'

b'We are not sleeping on important health issues. 4,000 employees have been screened for sleep apnea with 1,500 receiving treatment for this disorder. Southern Company invests in employees\xe2\x80\x99 well-being, equipping them with the tools to maintain a healthy routine. Link in bio.'

b'From drag racing superstar, to engineering supervisor, @alabamapower\xe2\x80\x99s TJ Pruitt keeps safety first. Read how our #EnergyBehindtheEnergy leads by example at \xe2\x80\x9cOur Culture\xe2\x80\x9d on Southern Company\xe2\x80\x99s career page as we celebrate National Engineers Week across the system! #eweek2020'
b'Today, we released our fourth-quarter and full-year 2019 earnings. View the full report using the link in bio.'
b'CEO Tom Fanning is scheduled to appear as a guest on Bloomberg TV Thursday, February 20, around 7:30 a.m. ET to discuss fourth-quarter and full-year 2019 earnings.'

b'Johnny Howze had to wear a tie every day to his first intern program with Southern Company\xe2\x80\x94little did he know this would tie him to our company 30 years later. Serving as vice president of Supply Chain Management, he is the 2020 executive sponsor for the @NSBE national conference, where he was first hired full-time in 1997. Link in bio.'
b'Another Vogtle Milestone! Workers at @ga_power\xe2\x80\x99s Vogtle 3 & 4 project have completed the final concrete placement inside the Unit 3 containment vessel. Link in bio.'

b'@southernpowerco\xe2\x80\x99s 100-megawatt Wildhorse Mountain Wind Facility is operational, becoming their fourth wind project within the state of Oklahoma. This excellent addition to their growing renewable fleet showcases Southern Power\xe2\x80\x99s commitment to the development of wind energy. Link in bio.'

b'Two of our outstanding attorneys, Kasey Chow and Ryan Smith, will participate in the Leadership Council for Legal Diversity\xe2\x80\x99s landmark Fellows Program. LDLC focuses on building relationships and leadership skills to continue diversifying the legal profession. Link in bio.'

b'Over the past decade, CEO Tom Fanning\xe2\x80\x99s approach to leadership has included a focus the performance and resilience of our business, but also on the broader economy and national security, as well being a leading voice in national energy policy. In the cover story of this edition of CEO Magazine, Fanning discusses the significant changes that have led to major successes. Link in bio.'

b"Celebrating our 4th consecutive year receiving a perfect score on @humanrightscampaign's Corporate Equality Index! We are proud to be named a Best Place to Work for LGBTQ Equality. Link in bio. #CEI2020 #SouthernCompany"

b'We are pleased to announce a $50 million multi-year initiative to provide students at historically black colleges and universities with scholarships, internships, leadership development, and access to technology and innovation to support career readiness. Link in bio.'

b'MLK Day was a day on for Southern Company, not a day off. Employees across our system honored Martin Luther King Jr\xe2\x80\x99s legacy and commitment to service through numerous volunteer projects in their communities.'

b'Celebrating our 9th year on @fortunemag\xe2\x80\x99s World\xe2\x80\x99s Most Admired Companies list! Thank you to our 29,000 employees across the system for making this possible. Link in bio. \n#MostAdmiredCos #SouthernCompany #fortunemagazine'
b'Remember. Celebrate. Act. #MLKDay #MLKDayofService'

b'Take a look at our stewardship successes in 2019, including $11.3 million towards on-the-ground conservation impact! In 2020, we want to do more. What should we work on conserving next? @nfwf \n#SouthernCompany #conservation #stewardship #2019review'
